09/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The main opposition party, VMRO-DPMNE, on Wednesday (8 October) invited the ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM) to prepare a common strategy for the country's integration into the EU. The document would include a timetable for meeting membership requirements.
In other news Wednesday, President Boris Trajkovski met with Japanese Emperor Akihito in Tokyo. They agreed to step up bilateral co-operation, especially in the economic sphere. Also under discussion is opening a Japanese embassy in Skopje. (Dnevnik - 09/10/03; MIA, Makfax - 08/10/03)
